Both fixes are done and compile cleanly. Here's a summary:
---
**Fix 1 – Kill warnings** (`managed_processes.rs`):  
Added `.stderr(Stdio::null())` to the `kill -KILL` command in `force_stop`. When a Chrome process has already exited, `kill` would write "No such process" to stderr; suppressing it eliminates the noise.
**Fix 2 – `test_e2e_storage` "Channel was cancelled"** (`e2e.rs`):  
Removed `kill_all_browsers()` from the per-scenario loop. It's now called inside `run_named_scenario` only when `restart_browser4 == true`. Previously it ran after every scenario — including `test_navigation` which intentionally leaves a session open for `test_storage` to continue — killing Chrome mid-session. The final cleanup call at the end of the main function is preserved.

